# Login Page

Component: `src/app/components/LoginPage.tsx`
Route: `/login` (default landing — `/` redirects to `/login`)

## Layout
- Full screen, two-panel: left branded + right form
- Left panel: `bg-[#004299]` gradient, centered white Paytm logo, phone mockup carousel
- Right panel: white, form centered with `max-w-[400px]`

## Form Fields
- Uses `TextField` component for both email and password
- Email: `<TextField label="Mobile Number or Email" />`
- Password: `<TextField label="Paytm Password" type="password" trailingIcon={<Eye|EyeOff/>} />`

## Button States
- **Disabled** (empty fields): `bg-[#ebebeb] text-[#acacac] cursor-not-allowed`
- **Enabled** (both filled): `bg-[#004299] text-white hover:bg-[#009de5]`
- Logic: `isDisabled = !email.trim() || !password.trim()`
- On click: `navigate("/home")`

## Links
- "Forgot Password": Subtle hyperlink, `ml-auto` (right-aligned)
- "terms of use", "privacy policy": Subtle hyperlinks (`font-normal`)
- "Create an account": Strong hyperlink (`font-semibold`)

## Autofill Handling
- Chrome autofill detection via `onAnimationStart` + CSS `@keyframes`
- Labels float correctly when browser autofills credentials
